//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
01. Setup
    https://github.com/understrap/understrap
    Download all the files from Understrap and Wordpress
    Create a website folder in any drive (name this folder as "root")
    Create a "www" folder in "root" folder
    Place all files downloaded from Wordpress into "www" folder
    .. > www > wp-content > themes
        Create a new folder in themes folder and name this "mytheme"
        Place ALL files from Understrap into "mytheme" folder


//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
02. Database Setup - PhpMyAdmin
    Start localhost/phpmyadmin
    In Database tab, crate database and name it "yourwebsite"
    Copy host folder from another website and paste into "root" folder
    Open the host folder and edit "host" file using notepad
        Add: 127.0.0.1 yourwebsite.localhost 

    Enter web browser: yourwebsite.localhost/wp-admin/setup-config.php
        Click on Let's Go button
        Database Name: yourwebsite
        Database Host: localhost
        Table Prefix: wp_
        Click submit and run installation
        Continue and install wordpress

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
03. Wordpress Theme Setup

    Setting up UnderStrap Theme
        Renaming: Open root >> www >> wp-content >> themes >> mytheme
            Do not select any file. Right click and open folder with VSCode
            Edit style.css
                Theme Name: Yourwebsite
        Replace picture: Open root >> www >> wp-content >> themes >> mytheme        
            Highlight "screenshot.jpg"
            Open and edit with Adobe
            Save and replace image
        Open Web Browser and enter yourwebsite.localhost/wp-admin/themes.php
            Open Side Menu >> Appearance >> Themes        
            Select Yourwebsite theme and click on "Activate"

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
04. Install and run Gulp
    Open VSCode and enter Terminal
    Type in "npm install" and enter //npm comes along with node.js as a package
    Type in "gulp watch" to run gulp
    
    #Test by changing the primary color
    Side Menu >> mytheme >> sass >> theme >> _theme_variables.scss
        $primary: #5533ff    //this will be the primary color in hex

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
05. Customize Wordpress Menu Bar

    Create "img" folder
        Store all images and logos into this folder

    Adding Menus
        Wordpress >> Side Menu >> Appearance >> Menus
        Add the menu required in Menu Structure
            Menu Settings >> Display: Primary Menu

        Open Side Menu >> mytheme >>  header.php >> wrapper-navbar >> main-nav >>             
            class="navbar navbar-expand-lg" aria-lebelledby="main-nav-label"
                //bg-primary sets background color to primary                 -- Remove
                //navbar-dark sets navigation to dark                         -- Remove
                //navbar-expand-md is responsive collapsing to mid size       -- Remove
                //navbar-expand-lg breaks at earlier point
            container > wp_nav_menu (); > array ()
                'menu_class' => 'navbar-nav', //ml-auto enables automatic resizing
    
        Add new file
            mytheme >> page-templates >> template-home.php
            Copy all codes from fullwidthpage.php to template-home.php
                Remove "<div class="wrapper">"
                Remove "if(is_front-page()){}"
                Remove "$container = get_theme_mod"
                Template: Home

        Wordpress >> yourwebsite.localhost
            Create a new page
                Click on +New >> Page
            Right hand menu
                Document >> Page attributes
                Template Name: Template: Home
                Click on Publish
                Return to Wordpress admin page
            Admin Page
                Dashboard >> Settings >> Reading
                    Your homepage displays: Static Page
                    Homepage: Home
                    Save Changes

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
06. Header (Layout, Navigation and CSS Styling)
    //mytheme >> page-templates >> template-home.php
        <?php
        /**
        @package understap
        */
        defined('ABSPATH') || exit;
        get_header();
        ?>
        
        <div class="home=banner">
        </div>
        
        <?php
        get_footer();

    //mytheme >> sass >> theme >> _theme.scss
        
        $primary: #223A47;                                          //Taken from ../_theme_variables.scss
        $secondary: F27257;                                         //For the secondary color on main menu whenever a Home menu is of different color
        #wrapper-navbar{                                            //To add spacing before the logo
            .top-header-holder {
                height: 260px;
                background:#f1f1f1;                
            }
            //#main-menu {                                          //Name taken from 'menu_id' in header.php, to apply across whole section, from browser inspect mode, you'll see <nav id="main-nav">, 
            #main-nav {                                             //replace #main-menu to #main-nav
                border-top:1px solid rgba(#5DA0AA, 0.5);            //where 0.5 is opacity
                border-bottom:1px solid rgba(#5DA0AA, 0.5);
                ul {                                                //Menu fonts and stylings
                    li {
                        a {
                            font-weight:600px;
                            font-size:22px;
                            text-transform: uppercase;
                        }
                        
                        &.current_page_item {                        //Home menu with different color, using the variable "$secondary" as secondary color
                            a {
                                color: $secondary;
                            }
                        }                        
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        .home-banner {
            height:1080px;
            background: #ccc;                                       //grey color
            background-image:url(../img/home-banner.jpg);           //resides in ../wp-content/themes/mytheme/img
            background-size:cover;
        }
    
    //mytheme >> sass >> theme >> _theme_variables.scss
        $primary: #223A47;                                          //Color of Main Menu fonts
    
    //mytheme > page-templates > header.php        
        div class="site" >> div id="wrapper-navbar" >>
                <div class="top-header-holder"></div>               //Add spacing before the logo. Add line above class "skip-link sr-onlyfocusable"


        div class="container" >> button class="navbar-toggler" >> 
            <?php
            wp_nav_menu(
                array(
                    'menu_id' => 'main-menu',                       //Name reference for #main-menu in _theme.scss
                )
            );



//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
07. Website Custom Fonts Imported Google and Menubar Layout and Styling
    
    Import fonts from fonts.google.com
        Search and select the fonts
        Click on "Select this style"
        Right hand panel, open "embed" tab
        Copy <link> and paste it into header.php, head section
        Copy CSS code and paste into _theme.scss
    
    //mytheme >> page-templates >> header.php  
        <head>
            <link rel="profile" href="..."> //Existing link
            *Paste copied link here*
            <?php wp_head(); ?>

    //mytheme >> sass >> theme >> _theme.scss
        Create a body function above #wrapper-navbar and paste the CSS code from google
        
        body {
            *Paste Google font CSS code here*
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height:1.25;
        }

    Add spaces between the menu titles
    //mytheme >> sass >> theme >> _theme.scss
        #wrapper-navbar {
            margin-bottom: -360px;
            #main-nav{ 
                padding: 0px;
                ul{
                    flex:1;                                           //Space between texts
                    justify-content: space-between; //Add space
                    li{
                        a{
                            padding:  1.5em 0.5em;  //add this line, 1.5em for y axis
                        }
                    }
                } 
            }
        }

